abstract_summ: In a previous article [1] we have described the temporal evolution of the Sars-Cov-2 in Italy in the time window February 24-April 1 . In this article our goal is to study the missing peak, i.e. the currently infected one (or total currently positive) After the April 7 the large increase in the number of swabs meant that the logistical behavior of the infected curve no longer worked . We think that this trend could be useful for a future epidemic of this coronavirus .
